 His sixteen-year-old daughter Laura died a few days later, leaving the family doubly bereft in the same week."},{"number":2,"category":"legacy","header":"His Pierpont land became Clover Dairy Farm","body":"The land he inherited had passed from Rev. James Pierpont to Lt. Joseph Pierpont to his father Giles to him — a four-generation Pierpont landholding. After his death it was sold and became Clover Dairy Farm under Dr. D.W. Patten."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Son became U.S. Attorney General under Grant","body":"His eldest son was baptized Munson Edwards Pierpont in 1813 — by first wife Eunice Munson, who died eight months later. The son later dropped 'Munson' and changed his surname to Pierrepont, serving as U.S. Attorney General under President Grant in 1875."}],"slug":"giles-pierpont-jr-1783"},"X00481":{"id":"X00481","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"tags":[],"sources":[],"birth":{"year":1792},"death":{"year":1814},"gender":"female","number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"H00899","date_year":1808,"date_month":10,"date_day":26,"children_ids":["HD1492","HD1493"]}],"parents":{},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Eunice Munson","first_name":"Eunice","maiden_name":"Munson","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"eunice-munson-1792"},"X00482":{"id":"X00482","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_e