-Gaudens marble bust, gift of Mary Pierrepont Beckwith"},{"short":"Pierrepont, Edwards (1817-1892). Argument to the jury, trial of John H. Surratt (Govt. Print. Off., Washington, 1867)"},{"short":"Plain Dealer (Cleveland OH), Mar 7, 1892, p.7 — obituary"}],"birth":{"year":1813,"month":11,"day":4,"city":"North Haven","state":"Connecticut"},"death":{"year":1892,"month":3,"day":6,"city":"New York","state":"New York"},"political_offices":[{"title":"U.S. Attorney General","jurisdiction":"United States","dates":"1875-1876"},{"title":"U.S. Minister to Great Britain","jurisdiction":"United States","dates":"1876-1877"},{"title":"Judge Superior Court","jurisdiction":"New York City","dates":"1857-1860"},{"title":"U.S. Attorney","jurisdiction":"Southern District of New York","dates":"1869-1870"}],"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"X00483","children_ids":["HD1501","HD1502"],"marriage_number":1,"date_year":1846,"date_month":5,"date_day":27}],"cross_connections":[{"type":"family_connection","related_id":"HD1438","display_label":"Second cousins once removed via Lt. Joseph Pierpont","link_text":"Gov. Hobart Baldwin Bigelow"},{"type":"family_connection","related_id":"H00366","display_label":"Shared common ancestor — both descend from his Pierpont brother","link_text":"Joseph Pierpont"},{"type":"family_connection","related_id":"H00372","display_label":"Shared common ancestor — both descend from his Pierpont brother","link_text":"Giles Pierpont"}],"gender":"male","notable":{"is_notable":true,"notable_category":[],"notable_blurb":"U.S. Attorney General; Minister to Britain","primary_url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edwards_Pierrepont","primary_url_label":"Wikipedia"},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"career","header":"Attorney General who prosecuted the Whiskey Ring","body":"Appointed Attorney General by President Grant in 1875, he prosecuted the Whiskey Ring tax-evasion syndicate and obtained 110 convictions. He confronted Grant directly when the President's own secretary Orville Babcock was implicated."},{"number":2,"category":"law","header":"Prosecuted Lincoln assassination conspirator John Surratt","body":"In 1867 he was hired by the federal government to prosecute John H. Surratt, an alleged conspirator in Lincoln's assassination. His closing argument famously compared Surratt's testimony to 'lies generating perjuries… like flies in a rotting carcass' — but Surratt was acquitted by a hung jury."},{"number":3,"category":"law","header":"Helped overthrow the Tweed Ring in 1871","body":"As a leading member of New York's Committee of Seventy, he helped overthrow the Tammany Hall Tweed Ring in 1871. He was then serving as U.S. District Attorney for the Southern District of New York under Grant's appointment."},{"number":4,"category":"career","header":"Introduced former President Grant to Queen Victoria","body":"As U.S. Minister to Great Britain (1876-1877) he argued successfully that Grant deserved royal precedence as a former head of state. 'Once a President always a President,' he said — and introduced Grant to Queen Victoria at Windsor Castle."},{"number":5,"category":"character","header":"Phrenologist who wanted his bust enlarged like Plato","body":"In 1874 he commissioned Augustus Saint-Gaudens for a marble bust and kept asking him to enlarge his head to resemble Socrates and Plato. Saint-Gaudens wrote that the finished bust 'seemed to be affected with some dreadful swelling disease.'"}],"number_of_marriages":1,"bio":{"display_name":"Edwards Pierrepont","first_name":"Edwards","last_name":"Pierrepont","middle_name":"Pierrepont","maiden_name":"Pierpont","married_names":[],"photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1777433839/Edwards-Pierrepont1.23.21-e1611512932494_qj97ls.jpg"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST010"},{"institution_id":"INST022","relationship":"alumnus","years":"1837"}],"landmarks":[],"artwork